18EC_KEY *EC_KEY_new(void)
19{
20 return EC_KEY_new_method(NULL);
21}
22
23EC_KEY *EC_KEY_new_by_curve_name(int nid)
24{
25 EC_KEY *ret = EC_KEY_new();
26 if (ret == NULL)
27 return NULL;
28 ret->group = EC_GROUP_new_by_curve_name(nid);
29 if (ret->group == NULL) {
30 EC_KEY_free(ret);
31 return NULL;
32 }
33 if (ret->meth->set_group != NULL
34 && ret->meth->set_group(ret, ret->group) == 0) {
35 EC_KEY_free(ret);
36 return NULL;
37 }
38 return ret;
39}
40
41void EC_KEY_free(EC_KEY *r)
42{
43 int i;
44
45 if (r == NULL)
46 return;
47
48 CRYPTO_DOWN_REF(&r->references, &i, r->lock);
49 REF_PRINT_COUNT("EC_KEY", r);
50 if (i > 0)
51 return;
52 REF_ASSERT_ISNT(i < 0);
53
54 if (r->meth != NULL && r->meth->finish != NULL)
55 r->meth->finish(r);
56
57#ifndef OPENSSL_NO_ENGINE
58 ENGINE_finish(r->engine);
59#endif
60
61 if (r->group && r->group->meth->keyfinish)
62 r->group->meth->keyfinish(r);
63
64 CRYPTO_free_ex_data(CRYPTO_EX_INDEX_EC_KEY, r, &r->ex_data);
65 CRYPTO_THREAD_lock_free(r->lock);
66 EC_GROUP_free(r->group);
67 EC_POINT_free(r->pub_key);
68 BN_clear_free(r->priv_key);
69
70 OPENSSL_clear_free((void *)r, sizeof(EC_KEY));
71}

73EC_KEY *EC_KEY_copy(EC_KEY *dest, const EC_KEY *src)
74{
75 if (dest == NULL || src == NULL) {
76 ECerr(EC_F_EC_KEY_COPY, ERR_R_PASSED_NULL_PARAMETER);
77 return NULL;
78 }
79 if (src->meth != dest->meth) {
80 if (dest->meth->finish != NULL)
81 dest->meth->finish(dest);
82 if (dest->group && dest->group->meth->keyfinish)
83 dest->group->meth->keyfinish(dest);
84#ifndef OPENSSL_NO_ENGINE
85 if (ENGINE_finish(dest->engine) == 0)
86 return 0;
87 dest->engine = NULL;
88#endif
89 }
90 /* copy the parameters */
91 if (src->group != NULL) {
92 const EC_METHOD *meth = EC_GROUP_method_of(src->group);
93 /* clear the old group */
94 EC_GROUP_free(dest->group);
95 dest->group = EC_GROUP_new(meth);
96 if (dest->group == NULL)
97 return NULL;
98 if (!EC_GROUP_copy(dest->group, src->group))
99 return NULL;
100
101 /* copy the public key */
102 if (src->pub_key != NULL) {
103 EC_POINT_free(dest->pub_key);
104 dest->pub_key = EC_POINT_new(src->group);
105 if (dest->pub_key == NULL)
106 return NULL;
107 if (!EC_POINT_copy(dest->pub_key, src->pub_key))
108 return NULL;
109 }
110 /* copy the private key */
111 if (src->priv_key != NULL) {
112 if (dest->priv_key == NULL) {
113 dest->priv_key = BN_new();
114 if (dest->priv_key == NULL)
115 return NULL;
116 }
117 if (!BN_copy(dest->priv_key, src->priv_key))
118 return NULL;
119 if (src->group->meth->keycopy
120 && src->group->meth->keycopy(dest, src) == 0)
121 return NULL;
122 }
123 }
124
125 /* copy the rest */
126 dest->enc_flag = src->enc_flag;
127 dest->conv_form = src->conv_form;
128 dest->version = src->version;
129 dest->flags = src->flags;
130 if (!CRYPTO_dup_ex_data(CRYPTO_EX_INDEX_EC_KEY,
131 &dest->ex_data, &src->ex_data))
132 return NULL;
133
134 if (src->meth != dest->meth) {
135#ifndef OPENSSL_NO_ENGINE
136 if (src->engine != NULL && ENGINE_init(src->engine) == 0)
137 return NULL;
138 dest->engine = src->engine;
139#endif
140 dest->meth = src->meth;
141 }
142
143 if (src->meth->copy != NULL && src->meth->copy(dest, src) == 0)
144 return NULL;
145
146 return dest;
147}
148
149EC_KEY *EC_KEY_dup(const EC_KEY *ec_key)
150{
151 EC_KEY *ret = EC_KEY_new_method(ec_key->engine);
152
153 if (ret == NULL)
154 return NULL;
155
156 if (EC_KEY_copy(ret, ec_key) == NULL) {
157 EC_KEY_free(ret);
158 return NULL;
159 }
160 return ret;
161}
162
163int EC_KEY_up_ref(EC_KEY *r)
164{
165 int i;
166
167 if (CRYPTO_UP_REF(&r->references, &i, r->lock) <= 0)
168 return 0;
169
170 REF_PRINT_COUNT("EC_KEY", r);
171 REF_ASSERT_ISNT(i < 2);
172 return ((i > 1) ? 1 : 0);
173}

180int EC_KEY_generate_key(EC_KEY *eckey)
181{
182 if (eckey == NULL || eckey->group == NULL) {
183 ECerr(EC_F_EC_KEY_GENERATE_KEY, ERR_R_PASSED_NULL_PARAMETER);
184 return 0;
185 }
186 if (eckey->meth->keygen != NULL)
187 return eckey->meth->keygen(eckey);
188 ECerr(EC_F_EC_KEY_GENERATE_KEY, EC_R_OPERATION_NOT_SUPPORTED);
189 return 0;
190}

193{
194 return eckey->group->meth->keygen(eckey);
195}

197int ec_key_simple_generate_key(EC_KEY *eckey)
198{
199 int ok = 0;
200 BN_CTX *ctx = NULL;
201 BIGNUM *priv_key = NULL;
202 const BIGNUM *order = NULL;
203 EC_POINT *pub_key = NULL;
204
205 if ((ctx = BN_CTX_new()) == NULL)
206 goto err;
207
208 if (eckey->priv_key == NULL) {
209 priv_key = BN_new();
210 if (priv_key == NULL)
211 goto err;
212 } else
213 priv_key = eckey->priv_key;
214
215 order = EC_GROUP_get0_order(eckey->group);
216 if (order == NULL)
217 goto err;
218
219 do
220 if (!BN_priv_rand_range(priv_key, order))
221 goto err;
222 while (BN_is_zero(priv_key)) ;
223
224 if (eckey->pub_key == NULL) {
225 pub_key = EC_POINT_new(eckey->group);
226 if (pub_key == NULL)
227 goto err;
228 } else
229 pub_key = eckey->pub_key;
230
231 if (!EC_POINT_mul(eckey->group, pub_key, priv_key, NULL, NULL, ctx))
232 goto err;
233
234 eckey->priv_key = priv_key;
235 eckey->pub_key = pub_key;
236
237 ok = 1;
238
239 err:
240 if (eckey->pub_key == NULL)
241 EC_POINT_free(pub_key);
242 if (eckey->priv_key != priv_key)
243 BN_free(priv_key);
244 BN_CTX_free(ctx);
245 return ok;
246}

248int ec_key_simple_generate_public_key(EC_KEY *eckey)
249{
250 return EC_POINT_mul(eckey->group, eckey->pub_key, eckey->priv_key, NULL,
251 NULL, NULL);
252}

254int EC_KEY_check_key(const EC_KEY *eckey)
255{
256 if (eckey == NULL || eckey->group == NULL || eckey->pub_key == NULL) {
257 ECerr(EC_F_EC_KEY_CHECK_KEY, ERR_R_PASSED_NULL_PARAMETER);
258 return 0;
259 }
260
261 if (eckey->group->meth->keycheck == NULL) {
262 ECerr(EC_F_EC_KEY_CHECK_KEY, ERR_R_SHOULD_NOT_HAVE_BEEN_CALLED);
263 return 0;
264 }
265
266 return eckey->group->meth->keycheck(eckey);
267}
268
269int ec_key_simple_check_key(const EC_KEY *eckey)
270{
271 int ok = 0;
272 BN_CTX *ctx = NULL;
273 const BIGNUM *order = NULL;
274 EC_POINT *point = NULL;
275
276 if (eckey == NULL || eckey->group == NULL || eckey->pub_key == NULL) {
277 ECerr(EC_F_EC_KEY_SIMPLE_CHECK_KEY, ERR_R_PASSED_NULL_PARAMETER);
278 return 0;
279 }
280
281 if (EC_POINT_is_at_infinity(eckey->group, eckey->pub_key)) {
282 ECerr(EC_F_EC_KEY_SIMPLE_CHECK_KEY, EC_R_POINT_AT_INFINITY);
283 goto err;
284 }
285
286 if ((ctx = BN_CTX_new()) == NULL)
287 goto err;
288 if ((point = EC_POINT_new(eckey->group)) == NULL)
289 goto err;
290
291 /* testing whether the pub_key is on the elliptic curve */
292 if (EC_POINT_is_on_curve(eckey->group, eckey->pub_key, ctx) <= 0) {
293 ECerr(EC_F_EC_KEY_SIMPLE_CHECK_KEY, EC_R_POINT_IS_NOT_ON_CURVE);
294 goto err;
295 }
296 /* testing whether pub_key * order is the point at infinity */
297 order = eckey->group->order;
298 if (BN_is_zero(order)) {
299 ECerr(EC_F_EC_KEY_SIMPLE_CHECK_KEY, EC_R_INVALID_GROUP_ORDER);
300 goto err;
301 }
302 if (!EC_POINT_mul(eckey->group, point, NULL, eckey->pub_key, order, ctx)) {
303 ECerr(EC_F_EC_KEY_SIMPLE_CHECK_KEY, ERR_R_EC_LIB);
304 goto err;
305 }
306 if (!EC_POINT_is_at_infinity(eckey->group, point)) {
307 ECerr(EC_F_EC_KEY_SIMPLE_CHECK_KEY, EC_R_WRONG_ORDER);
308 goto err;
309 }
310 /*
311 * in case the priv_key is present : check if generator * priv_key ==
312 * pub_key
313 */
314 if (eckey->priv_key != NULL) {
315 if (BN_cmp(eckey->priv_key, order) >= 0) {
316 ECerr(EC_F_EC_KEY_SIMPLE_CHECK_KEY, EC_R_WRONG_ORDER);
317 goto err;
318 }
319 if (!EC_POINT_mul(eckey->group, point, eckey->priv_key,
320 NULL, NULL, ctx)) {
321 ECerr(EC_F_EC_KEY_SIMPLE_CHECK_KEY, ERR_R_EC_LIB);
322 goto err;
323 }
324 if (EC_POINT_cmp(eckey->group, point, eckey->pub_key, ctx) != 0) {
325 ECerr(EC_F_EC_KEY_SIMPLE_CHECK_KEY, EC_R_INVALID_PRIVATE_KEY);
326 goto err;
327 }
328 }
329 ok = 1;
330 err:
331 BN_CTX_free(ctx);
332 EC_POINT_free(point);
333 return ok;
334}
335
336int EC_KEY_set_public_key_affine_coordinates(EC_KEY *key, BIGNUM *x,
337 BIGNUM *y)
338{
339 BN_CTX *ctx = NULL;
340 BIGNUM *tx, *ty;
341 EC_POINT *point = NULL;
342 int ok = 0;
343
344 if (key == NULL || key->group == NULL || x == NULL || y == NULL) {
345 ECerr(EC_F_EC_KEY_SET_PUBLIC_KEY_AFFINE_COORDINATES,
346 ERR_R_PASSED_NULL_PARAMETER);
347 return 0;
348 }
349 ctx = BN_CTX_new();
350 if (ctx == NULL)
351 return 0;
352
353 BN_CTX_start(ctx);
354 point = EC_POINT_new(key->group);
355
356 if (point == NULL)
357 goto err;
358
359 tx = BN_CTX_get(ctx);
360 ty = BN_CTX_get(ctx);
361 if (ty == NULL)
362 goto err;
363
364 if (!EC_POINT_set_affine_coordinates(key->group, point, x, y, ctx))
365 goto err;
366 if (!EC_POINT_get_affine_coordinates(key->group, point, tx, ty, ctx))
367 goto err;
368
369 /*
370 * Check if retrieved coordinates match originals and are less than field
371 * order: if not values are out of range.
372 */
373 if (BN_cmp(x, tx) || BN_cmp(y, ty)
374 || (BN_cmp(x, key->group->field) >= 0)
375 || (BN_cmp(y, key->group->field) >= 0)) {
376 ECerr(EC_F_EC_KEY_SET_PUBLIC_KEY_AFFINE_COORDINATES,
377 EC_R_COORDINATES_OUT_OF_RANGE);
378 goto err;
379 }
380
381 if (!EC_KEY_set_public_key(key, point))
382 goto err;
383
384 if (EC_KEY_check_key(key) == 0)
385 goto err;
386
387 ok = 1;
388
389 err:
390 BN_CTX_end(ctx);
391 BN_CTX_free(ctx);
392 EC_POINT_free(point);
393 return ok;
394
395}

402int EC_KEY_set_group(EC_KEY *key, const EC_GROUP *group)
403{
404 if (key->meth->set_group != NULL && key->meth->set_group(key, group) == 0)
405 return 0;
406 EC_GROUP_free(key->group);
407 key->group = EC_GROUP_dup(group);
408 return (key->group == NULL) ? 0 : 1;
409}

411const BIGNUM *EC_KEY_get0_private_key(const EC_KEY *key)
412{
413 return key->priv_key;
414}
415
416int EC_KEY_set_private_key(EC_KEY *key, const BIGNUM *priv_key)
417{
418 if (key->group == NULL || key->group->meth == NULL)
419 return 0;
420 if (key->group->meth->set_private != NULL
421 && key->group->meth->set_private(key, priv_key) == 0)
422 return 0;
423 if (key->meth->set_private != NULL
424 && key->meth->set_private(key, priv_key) == 0)
425 return 0;
426 BN_clear_free(key->priv_key);
427 key->priv_key = BN_dup(priv_key);
428 return (key->priv_key == NULL) ? 0 : 1;
429}

433 return key->pub_key;

436int EC_KEY_set_public_key(EC_KEY *key, const EC_POINT *pub_key)
437{
438 if (key->meth->set_public != NULL
439 && key->meth->set_public(key, pub_key) == 0)
440 return 0;
441 EC_POINT_free(key->pub_key);
442 key->pub_key = EC_POINT_dup(pub_key, key->group);
443 return (key->pub_key == NULL) ? 0 : 1;
444}

496size_t EC_KEY_key2buf(const EC_KEY *key, point_conversion_form_t form,
497 unsigned char **pbuf, BN_CTX *ctx)
498{
499 if (key == NULL || key->pub_key == NULL || key->group == NULL)
500 return 0;
501 return EC_POINT_point2buf(key->group, key->pub_key, form, pbuf, ctx);
502}
503
504int EC_KEY_oct2key(EC_KEY *key, const unsigned char *buf, size_t len,
505 BN_CTX *ctx)
506{
507 if (key == NULL || key->group == NULL)
508 return 0;
509 if (key->pub_key == NULL)
510 key->pub_key = EC_POINT_new(key->group);
511 if (key->pub_key == NULL)
512 return 0;
513 if (EC_POINT_oct2point(key->group, key->pub_key, buf, len, ctx) == 0)
514 return 0;
515 /*
516 * Save the point conversion form.
517 * For non-custom curves the first octet of the buffer (excluding
518 * the last significant bit) contains the point conversion form.
519 * EC_POINT_oct2point() has already performed sanity checking of
520 * the buffer so we know it is valid.
521 */
522 if ((key->group->meth->flags & EC_FLAGS_CUSTOM_CURVE) == 0)
523 key->conv_form = (point_conversion_form_t)(buf[0] & ~0x01);
524 return 1;
525}

527size_t EC_KEY_priv2oct(const EC_KEY *eckey,
528 unsigned char *buf, size_t len)
529{
530 if (eckey->group == NULL || eckey->group->meth == NULL)
531 return 0;
532 if (eckey->group->meth->priv2oct == NULL) {
533 ECerr(EC_F_EC_KEY_PRIV2OCT, ERR_R_SHOULD_NOT_HAVE_BEEN_CALLED);
534 return 0;
535 }
536
537 return eckey->group->meth->priv2oct(eckey, buf, len);
538}
539
540size_t ec_key_simple_priv2oct(const EC_KEY *eckey,
541 unsigned char *buf, size_t len)
542{
543 size_t buf_len;
544
545 buf_len = (EC_GROUP_order_bits(eckey->group) + 7) / 8;
546 if (eckey->priv_key == NULL)
547 return 0;
548 if (buf == NULL)
549 return buf_len;
550 else if (len < buf_len)
551 return 0;
552
553 /* Octetstring may need leading zeros if BN is to short */
554
555 if (BN_bn2binpad(eckey->priv_key, buf, buf_len) == -1) {
556 ECerr(EC_F_EC_KEY_SIMPLE_PRIV2OCT, EC_R_BUFFER_TOO_SMALL);
557 return 0;
558 }
559
560 return buf_len;
561}

564{
565 if (eckey->group == NULL || eckey->group->meth == NULL)

568 ECerr(EC_F_EC_KEY_OCT2PRIV, ERR_R_SHOULD_NOT_HAVE_BEEN_CALLED);
569 return 0;
570 }
571 return eckey->group->meth->oct2priv(eckey, buf, len);
572}
573
574int ec_key_simple_oct2priv(EC_KEY *eckey, const unsigned char *buf, size_t len)
575{
576 if (eckey->priv_key == NULL)
577 eckey->priv_key = BN_secure_new();
578 if (eckey->priv_key == NULL) {
579 ECerr(EC_F_EC_KEY_SIMPLE_OCT2PRIV, ERR_R_MALLOC_FAILURE);
580 return 0;
581 }
582 eckey->priv_key = BN_bin2bn(buf, len, eckey->priv_key);
583 if (eckey->priv_key == NULL) {
584 ECerr(EC_F_EC_KEY_SIMPLE_OCT2PRIV, ERR_R_BN_LIB);
585 return 0;
586 }
587 return 1;
588}
589
590size_t EC_KEY_priv2buf(const EC_KEY *eckey, unsigned char **pbuf)
591{
592 size_t len;
593 unsigned char *buf;
594
595 len = EC_KEY_priv2oct(eckey, NULL, 0);
596 if (len == 0)
597 return 0;
598 if ((buf = OPENSSL_malloc(len)) == NULL) {
599 ECerr(EC_F_EC_KEY_PRIV2BUF, ERR_R_MALLOC_FAILURE);
600 return 0;
601 }
602 len = EC_KEY_priv2oct(eckey, buf, len);
603 if (len == 0) {
604 OPENSSL_free(buf);
605 return 0;
606 }
607 *pbuf = buf;
608 return len;
609}
610
611int EC_KEY_can_sign(const EC_KEY *eckey)
612{
613 if (eckey->group == NULL || eckey->group->meth == NULL
614 || (eckey->group->meth->flags & EC_FLAGS_NO_SIGN))
615 return 0;
616 return 1;
617}
